definition: of the blackest black, an artificially produced flow of water, issue in a jet
details:
adjective
- of the blackest black
= example: of the blackest black
= synonyms: pitchy
noun
- an artificially produced flow of water
= synonyms: fountain
- an airplane powered by one or more jet engines
= synonyms: jet plane
- street names for ketamine
= synonyms: green
- the occurrence of a sudden discharge (as of liquid)
= synonyms: spirt, squirt, spurt
- atmospheric discharges (lasting 10 msec) bursting from the tops of giant storm clouds in blue cones that widen as they flash upward
= synonyms: blue jet, reverse lightning
- a hard black form of lignite that takes a brilliant polish and is used in jewelry or ornamentation
verb
- issue in a jet
= example: issue in a jet
= synonyms: gush
- fly a jet plane
